ArcSign — Blacklist Offline Seed Attribution
============================================

This directory ships an embedded (go:embed) offline seed for the transaction
blacklist so the security check works on first sign and offline.

ofac_sanctioned.txt
-------------------
US Treasury OFAC sanctioned digital-currency addresses (Ethereum). OFAC's
sanctions data is published by the U.S. government and is in the public domain.
Mirror used for convenience:
  https://github.com/0xB10C/ofac-sanctioned-digital-currency-addresses
  File: lists/sanctioned_addresses_ETH.json
Only the factual address data is redistributed (lowercased, sorted, de-duped).

MEW / Revoke (MIT) addresses
----------------------------
The seed ALSO includes the MIT-licensed MEW ethereum-lists + Revoke
approval-exploit-list addresses, reused at runtime from
internal/provider/data/malicious_spenders.txt (see that directory's NOTICE for
full MIT attribution). They are NOT re-vendored here — the blacklist seed loads
them from the provider package's already-embedded data.

Deliberately NOT embedded
-------------------------
ScamSniffer's address/domain data is GPL-licensed and cannot be vendored into
this Apache-2.0 repository. It is fetched at runtime (download-and-use, not
re-distribution) by the online Update path, alongside MetaMask phishing data.

Regeneration
------------
Refresh ofac_sanctioned.txt with:
  curl -fsSL "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/0xB10C/ofac-sanctioned-digital-currency-addresses/lists/sanctioned_addresses_ETH.json" \
    | jq -r '.[]' | tr 'A-Z' 'a-z' | grep -E '^0x[0-9a-f]{40}$' | sort -u
The seed is embedded statically and ships with the app version (offline / privacy-preserving).
